Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop them onto a
#large baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @dried oregano{1%sachet}, then
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.
> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1} and slice into 1cm thick rounds.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat. When hot, add
the courgette and cook until charred, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Turn only every couple of mins - this will result in the courgette
picking up some nice colour.

Once cooked, transfer the courgette to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Pop the sliced pepper and @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} onto another large baking
tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Roast on the middle shelf until soft and slightly charred, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, combine the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml},
@fresh pesto{32%g}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. This is your pesto dressing.

Once the veg has roasted, add everything to the bowl of pesto dressing and toss
to coat.

Just before serving, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g}, @diced British chicken breast{260%g}
and charred courgette to the bowl, then toss to combine.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

Share the chicken salad between your #bowls{}.

Crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} to finish.

Enjoy!